review_blob: The Great PumpKin King! If you havent tried it, try it. My favorite pumpkin beer thus far in 2012
beer_name: Samuel Adams Fat Jack Double Pumpkin

review_blob: I hope I can get my household guests to drink this one or else it may sit in the fridge until I get desperate.

Not a bad beer. I was surprised by the by the two companies working together but very excited to try the outcome. Im a huge Founders fan and this beer didnt really have that founders edge I look for when drinking theyre brews.
beer_name: Green Flash / Founders Linchpin White India Pale Ale

review_blob: Great Brew. Cant wait for the new Chicago brewery. Though I think its actually a Black IPA
Surprised how good this beer was. A hop heads true I.P.A.. After trying this beer, I look forward to trying many more beers from Sierra Nevada.

Hopothesis, I expected a lot out of you and all I was left with was a dry mouth and a the question of "wheres the hops". I generally dont care for malty IPAs but all and all this beer isnt bad tasting. I would say give it a try, but  dont commit to a full six pack at first.

beer_brewer_name: Coney Island Brewing Company (Boston Beer Company)
review_blob: Im a fan of almost anything barrel aged. I havent been a huge fan of Coney Islands brews in the past, but I can honestly say this one is worth a try. Great taste and good aroma, and definitely a good bang for your buck.  I bought the 22 oz. bomber and drank it from my beer snifter.
beer_name: Coney Island Human Blockhead - Barrel Aged

review_blob: I poured this New Belgium Black ale from a 12 oz. bottle into a tulip style beer stein. It poured dark, frothy, almost coffee like in color with the aroma of toffee and malt.  Tastes dry though strong in flavor with roasted malts and bitter coffee. Overall a good beer, but not my style.
